# Jetpack Compose Patterns

## State Hoisting
Composables must be stateless — hoist state to the caller or ViewModel:
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — state owned inside composable
@Composable fun SearchBar() {
    var query by remember { mutableStateOf("") }
    ...
}

// ✅ GOOD — state hoisted
@Composable fun SearchBar(query: String, onQueryChange: (String) -> Unit) { ... }
```

## Screen vs Component Split
- `*Screen.kt` — connects to ViewModel, collects state, passes to content composable
- `*Content.kt` / small composables — pure UI, no ViewModel dependency, fully previewable

```kotlin
@Composable
fun HomeScreen(viewModel: HomeViewModel = hiltViewModel()) {
    val uiState by viewModel.uiState.collectAsStateWithLifecycle()
    HomeContent(uiState = uiState, onRefresh = viewModel::refresh)
}

@Composable
fun HomeContent(uiState: HomeUiState, onRefresh: () -> Unit) { ... }
```

## Loading / Error / Empty States
Every screen that loads data must handle all four states:
```kotlin
when (uiState) {
    is Loading -> LoadingIndicator()
    is Success -> RideList(uiState.rides)
    is Empty   -> EmptyState(message = "No rides available")
    is Error   -> ErrorState(message = uiState.message, onRetry = onRefresh)
}
```

## Offer Countdown Timer
The 10-minute offer expiry timer must use `LaunchedEffect` + `rememberSaveable`:
```kotlin
LaunchedEffect(offer.expiresAt) {
    while (remaining > 0) {
        delay(1_000)
        remaining = offer.expiresAt - Clock.System.now()
    }
    onExpired()
}
```

## Preview Every Composable
```kotlin
@Preview(showBackground = true)
@Composable
fun RideCardPreview() = ShareWindTheme { RideCard(ride = previewRide) }
```

## Use Design System Tokens

Colors, typography, and shapes come from [docs/ui-mockups.md](https://github.com/lyhuynh323/ShareWind/blob/main/docs/ui-mockups.md). Use Material 3 theme tokens:

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded color
Text(color = Color(0xFF1A73E8))

// ✅ GOOD — theme tokens
Text(color = MaterialTheme.colorScheme.primary)
Text(style = MaterialTheme.typography.headlineLarge)
Surface(shape = MaterialTheme.shapes.large) { ... }
```

For semantic colors (Success, Warning, Accent) use `Color.kt`: `Success`, `Warning`, `Accent`.
